			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AE kit in PoV easy<a name="34989"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 16 04 10:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>AE kit PoV easy
<br />

<br />
If you want to train for AE kit without too much trouble, I would suggest you to try AE kit in PoV.
<br />

<br />
What you need :
<br />
_ Run speed 3 (if you have rs 5 it will not work properly)
<br />

<br />
Song lineup :
<br />
_ Melody of Mischief (62)
<br />
_ Chords of Dissonance (2)
<br />
_ Denon’s Discord (18)
<br />
_ Denon’s Bereavement (59)
<br />
_ DA
<br />
_ Marr (or any heal song)
<br />

<br />
The only problem you will encounter is that maybee the zone will be &#171; over &#187; camped.
<br />
Because the only mobs you will kit are the golems (north of PoV, in the wasteland).
<br />

<br />
Go north of the zone in the wasteland. Put a lute in your hand, then start selo. Go grab as much as golems as you can (just with proximity agro). Do not worry if you have adds, you will have a lot anyway. If you are lucky, you can have like 20+ golems running behind you :p
<br />
The trick is that the golems run faster than all the others mobs (they will never catch you with rs3), so you can do large circle and the songs will reach them :
<br />

<br />
_ target one golem (to see how your AE is going on).
<br />
_ stop selo.
<br />
_ begin to go round in circles, large at first, then tighter and tighter. (you don’t have to do very tight circles as the other AE kit, you’ll see the golems take the dots soon).
<br />
_ when all the golems are dead (grats xp<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />), you can start selo and fade or zone.
<br />

<br />
I got around 5 to 6%AA per mob at 65. If you get all of them, you’ll do around 1AA every 20 minutes.
<br />

<br />
I usually AE kit at NE wall, or sometimes near the wall of the zone in front of EC.
<br />

<br />
Good luck bards )
<br />

<br />
Ie : thank you very much to Xegonybard who write a great guide about AE kit<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Valaba Noirac 
<br />
Bard 
<br />
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150528
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
