<br />

<br />
Update~  I have seen the light.  Thanks for this guide.  I had to find my own way of learning this skill.  I don't do circles so much as constand running and turn left then right.  I found that with Run3 I can control how fast they gain on me by going straight to pull away and slight turns to make them close their gap.
<br />
  
<br />
 I don't stay in one circle for more than a few laps.  I roam LC finding a few spots in LC that make good circles.  I also mix it up with a snake pattern of curving left then right landing my dot at our closest point then pointing forward to pull away for a step then turn left till they close in and Dot lands then back Right etc.....
<br />

<br />
  By the way... people seeing me kiting ten golems automatically assume I am getting tons of xp.  So far I fail more than I succeed.  If this is nerfed it will be from other people perspective that bards are always AE kiting bla bla.
<br />

<br />
  Truth is this is very high risk vs high reward.  The XP from AE kite is still not as good as XP groups that can grind out constant kills with no deaths.  Add in our deaths and wasted time on kites that didn't go well and were not really getting away with much.
<br />

<br />
-Ruser-</span></td>
