				<td colspan="2"><span>PoV wasteland, To Ae you need run3, You don't need EN aa to do this. Although it used to help a great deal but as far as I know is nerfed now.
<br />

<br />

<br />
My highest amount of AA xp was over 150% when EN worked. I don't pull like that anymore but can handle a dozen mobs easily.
<br />

<br />
You want to avoid the crawlers, their arggo range and run speed is to different from the other mobs. If you have spiders and Golems you will most likely kill the golems first because the spiders are slower and will stay out of AE range. You may start hitting the spiders when there is only a few golems left.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Everything mentioned in this posting is correct, grab the mobs, compact them and then start AEing. Circles do need to be tight if you want to hit them. I always looked at it this way the more time you spend AEing a pull the more chance you have of dying. So I try to stick 4 AE's on them each time.
<br />

<br />
With the new GoD AA (forget the name) It gives crits to Dot spells/songs even one point in this will have a huge improvement on the damage you do.
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't suggest doing this in wastelands until you are upper 60's in level. anything lower will prolly be too painfully long because of resist.
<br />

<br />
Also you should always respect groups that come into the wasteland. It's not cool to horde all this xp for yourself when this is a mass multi online game and other people want to level too. Golems are prolly the best xp for a group without being in BoT or higher tier,.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
