			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE kit in PoV easy<a name="37037"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 28 04 12:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I actually use selo to AE kite.  After the EN nerf I can only get 2 dots to land but its plenty.  Round up as many as you can (including spiders but avoid crawlers).  get to a spot where its generally flat, hit DA and pack them in close, you want them on top of eachother. Before DA runs out - hit left/right + up + Enter (to activate chat) and you're stuck in a circle.  Switch to 3rd person view, let DA fade.  If you've packed them in close enough before you started the circle you wont get hit and you can keep that circle forever (until you hit an arrow key).  A side note would be that if you hit CTRL while in your circle you no longer move left/right making it easy to adjust your circle if pressed at the right time.
<br />

<br />
From there I could only get 2 of the ae dots to land, but the trade off to killing them safer from killing them faster was worth it to me.  It's still extremely risky - one lag spike and you're a dead bard, and it takes a little longer (about 20minutes) because you're only hitting them with 2 dots.  So I wouldn't recommend tring it if you're on dial up, have distractions, or having problems with lag/video lag.
<br />

<br />
Also, you can talk to people while you AE kite since you're only twisting 2 and there are no key presses to keep your circle.  Something I'm greatly appreciative of.</span></td>
