				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE kit in PoV easy<a name="40258"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 10:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well Shass, I finally got the courage to try it out.  On a fine Saturday morning I awoke early and rushed to to PoV to do a camp check.  As usual for Stromm, PoV was not overly camped in the early morning.  The WW camp was actually 100% free of people.  I also checked in the zone and found a cleric friend of mine (one with a 96% rez.....which will be important later in the story) working the EW camp.  
<br />

<br />
So I headed to the area while sending /tells arranging to potential rezzes with Sidywen should things not work out well.  I had decent buffs on including a big fat Virtue.  I took a swing of coffee (no whiskey that early in the morning) and charged around gathering up golems.  I took a couple hits but nothing minor and ended up with about 7 golems on my tail.  I hit my DA and let them beat uselessly on me to get them in a nice tight group.  I switched to 3rd person view and started trying to run in a circle.  As soon as my DA ran out I cut it too close and was INSTANTLY beat on not-so-uselessly and got the LOADING......PLEASE WAIT message.  
<br />

<br />
Okay, I was prepared for that.  It's a learning process I figured.  No biggie.  I go back, loot up my body and decide to try again.  No virtue this time which turned out to be a mistake but I tried again and BAM......same results.  Thinking to myself that there was still hope I decided to try a third time.  This time I switch to first person view and scroll out so I am looking at my back and can see to either side of me.   Well, I ran and ran and ran.  I felt like Forrest Gump for a while.  But as I tightened my circle more and more I couldn't seem to land a single DoT song on even one measly golem.  Finally either I lagged or turned too sharp and again it was LOADING.....PLEASE WAIT time.  Lol.
<br />

<br />
Three deaths was the limit I had set for trying to learn that particular trick.  At least 3 deaths in one sitting.  I dragged all 3 bodies to Sidywen (thank you again Sid for taking time out from your exp'ing to help out) and got 3 rezzes.  I then went /afk while playing AE mana in repayment since the cleric wouldn't take any donations.  
<br />

<br />
I've since thought about it and come to the conclusion that AE kiting in PoV is bad for my health.  Both Bardtail's, and mine.  My stress level was slightly higher, blood pressure had increased markedly, and my coffee intake was about double the norm.  Oh well.  
<br />

<br />
The best thing about a bard is there are many many different ways to skin a cat.  I just prefer not to let the golems do it for me!!  I went to BoT and grouped.  Dinged 64 this weekend.  I hope there are those of you who can AE kite golems in PoV but I'll stand back and watch from now on!!  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
